# Copy to .codesign.env for machine-local Azad signing settings.
#
# `just install` works without this file. Set AZAD_CODESIGN_IDENTITY only on
# development machines where you want macOS TCC permissions to survive rebuilds.
#
# Prefer the 40-character certificate hash from:
#   security find-identity -v -p codesigning "$HOME/Library/Keychains/login.keychain-db"
#
# AZAD_CODESIGN_IDENTITY="0123456789ABCDEF0123456789ABCDEF01234567"
#
# Maintainer-only release builds also use this file when running `just dist`
# locally. GitHub Actions sets these values through environment variables.
#
# Public distribution builds must be signed with Developer ID and notarized.
# The notarization profile is created outside the repo with:
#   xcrun notarytool store-credentials "azad-notarization"
#
# AZAD_VERSION="0.1.1"
# AZAD_SIGNING_IDENTITY="Developer ID Application: Example, Inc. (TEAMID1234)"
# AZAD_NOTARIZATION_PROFILE="azad-notarization"
#
# Explicit environment variables override this file.
